OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,FFormer Taoiseach Leo Varadkar has said
OL,6,Fthat the prospect of a Reform UK
OL,7,Fgovernment in Westminster would
OL,8,F'destabilise' the union in a similar
OL,9,Fway to Brexit.
OL,11,FVaradkar, who served as Taoiseach from
OL,12,F2017 to 2020 and from 2022 to 2024,
OL,13,Fwas involved in the Brexit
OL,14,Fnegotiations at a time when the border
OL,15,Fbetween Northern Ireland from the
OL,16,FRepublic of Ireland was a central
OL,17,Fissue.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,FWhen asked if he had concerns about
OL,6,Fthe future of the UK-EU relationship,
OL,7,FMr Varadkar said: "In the same way
OL,8,Fthat Brexit destabilised the union -
OL,9,FScotland and Northern Ireland - a
OL,10,FReform UK government doubling down on
OL,11,FBrexit and going for a harder Brexit,
OL,12,Fwould do the same thing again."
OL,14,FMr Varadkar was speaking to UTV's
OL,15,F'View from Stormont' to mark the 10th
OL,16,Fanniversary of the Brexit referendum,
OL,17,Fwhich took place on 23rd June 2016.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,FIn the referendum, 51% of voters in
OL,6,Fthe United Kingdom voted to leave the
OL,7,FEuropean Union, while 49% voted to
OL,8,Fremain. In Northern Ireland, 55% voted
OL,9,Fto remain, while 44% voted to leave.
OL,11,FIn 2018, Varadkar was heavily
OL,12,Fcriticised by unionists when he showed
OL,13,FEU leaders an Irish Times article
OL,14,Fabout the IRA bombing of a customs
OL,15,Fpost in 1972, warning of the
OL,16,Fpossibility of violence if a hard
OL,17,Fborder was pursued as a resolution
OL,18,Fduring the Brexit negotiations.
OL,20,FWhen asked if he regretted the move he
OL,21,Fwas defiant.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,F"No, I don't," he told UTV.
OL,7,F"Bear in mind what I was doing there,
OL,8,Fis I was reflecting advice that we
OL,9,Fwere getting from both the Garda
OL,10,FCommissioner and the Chief Constable,
OL,11,Fthat a hard border between the two
OL,12,Fparts of the island could lead to
OL,13,Fviolence.
OL,15,F"This was not just my opinion. This
OL,16,Fwas the security assessment in both
OL,17,Fjurisdictions. I wasn't threatening
OL,18,Fviolence. I was warning and repeating
OL,19,Fthe warning that there could be a
OL,20,Freturn to violence."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,FMr Varadkar went on: "I do remember a
OL,6,Funionist leader saying to me, who will
OL,7,Fremain unnamed, that they expected to
OL,8,Fbe betrayed by conservative prime
OL,9,Fministers."
OL,11,FWhen asked if he would do anything
OL,12,Fdifferently, Mr Varadkar said it would
OL,13,Fhave been to work 'harder' to get a
OL,14,Fbetter deal for Theresa May.
OL,16,F"I think perhaps from the EU side, not
OL,17,Fjust from Ireland's side, we could
OL,18,Fhave perhaps done more to help her get
OL,19,Fa deal through.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,F"However, the difficulty there was
OL,6,Fthat we were never all that convinced
OL,7,Fthat she would be able to get a deal
OL,8,Fthrough, and she simply wasn't as
OL,9,Fruthless as Boris Johnson when it came
OL,10,Fto dealing with her own party.
OL,12,F"Ultimately, the deal that we
OL,13,Fnegotiated with Prime Minister May -
OL,14,Fthe backstop - to me is still better,
OL,15,Fwould have been a better outcome for
OL,16,FIreland, Northern Ireland and all of
OL,17,Fthe UK than where we ended up in the
OL,18,Fend.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,F"But, I think, I think the difficulty
OL,6,Fthere was that it was never clear from
OL,7,Fthe UK government and certainly the UK
OL,8,Fparliament, what they actually wanted,
OL,9,Fand it was never clear to us that the
OL,10,FUK Prime Minister could get any deal
OL,11,Fthrough."
OL,13,FUTV also spoke to Lord Frost, who
OL,14,Fserved as the UK's chief Brexit
OL,15,Fnegotiator under Prime Minister Boris
OL,16,FJohnson.
OL,18,FLord Frost told 'View from Stormont'
OL,19,Fthat when it comes to Brexit: 'the job
OL,20,Fis done.'
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,F"The country is out of the EU for
OL,6,Fvirtually every purpose and I think it
OL,7,Fhas been a great period. Despite all
OL,8,Fthe twists and turns, we're getting
OL,9,Fused to independence. Our political
OL,10,Flife is coming back, and the country
OL,11,Fhas got a great future outside the
OL,12,FEuropean Union."
OL,14,FLord Frost was a central figure in
OL,15,Festablishing the Northern Ireland
OL,16,FProtocol - part of the Brexit deal
OL,17,Fsigned up to by Boris Johnson's
OL,18,Fgovernment that prevented a hard Irish
OL,19,Fborder by keeping Northern Ireland
OL,20,Finside the EU's single market for
OL,21,Fgoods.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,FAs a consequence, it created a trade
OL,6,Fborder between Northern Ireland and
OL,7,Fthe rest of the UK.
OL,9,FThe implementation of the Protocol
OL,10,Fresulted in demonstrations and
OL,11,Fprotests across Northern Ireland, and
OL,12,Feventually led to the collapse of the
OL,13,FStormont institutions when the DUP
OL,14,Fremoved Paul Givan as First Minister
OL,15,Fin 2022.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,FWhen it was put to Lord Frost that
OL,6,Fsome unionists blame him for creating
OL,7,Fthe Irish Sea border, he said: "My
OL,8,Fexperience is that most unionists are
OL,9,Funderstanding of the pressures that
OL,10,Fled us to agree it, recognised that we
OL,11,Fwere pushed to a place that we
OL,12,Fwouldn't have voluntarily got to and
OL,13,Fdid everything we could to improve the
OL,14,Farrangements after that."
OL,16,FIn a bid to appease unionist concerns
OL,17,Fand get Stormont power sharing
OL,18,Frestored, Prime Minister Rishi Sunak
OL,19,Fagreed a joint EU/UK accord known as
OL,20,Fthe Windsor Framework, which replaced
OL,21,Fthe Northern Ireland Protocol, in 2024.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,FThe framework requires checks and
OL,6,Fcustoms paperwork on goods moving from
OL,7,FGreat Britain into Northern Ireland.
OL,9,FIt also includes a series of measures
OL,10,Fdesigned to address concerns that
OL,11,Fpoliticians and businesses in Northern
OL,12,FIreland have a limited role in
OL,13,Finfluencing the post-Brexit rules that
OL,14,Fapply in the region.
OL,16,FLord Frost criticised the Windsor
OL,17,FFramework arrangements.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,F"I don't think they're sustainable. I
OL,6,Fthink we will need to return to those
OL,7,Fat some point because you can't have
OL,8,Fparts of the country governed by laws
OL,9,Fthat it gets no say in."
OL,11,FA debate over the future of the UK-EU
OL,12,Frelationship has reignited after Sir
OL,13,FKeir Starmer made closer ties with
OL,14,FBrussels a key pillar of his "reset"
OL,15,Fin the wake of Labour's seismic May
OL,16,Felection losses.
OL,18,FLord Frost warned against the move.
OL,26,@vD@^OUvD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,F"It's very dangerous, as this Labour
OL,6,Fgovernment seems to think, that there
OL,7,Fis some nirvana recoverable by going
OL,8,Fback closer to the European Union. It
OL,9,Fis simply not going to happen and the
OL,10,Fbest chance for success of this
OL,11,Fcountry is to get used to governing
OL,12,Fourselves properly and taking the
OL,13,Fbenefits.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,413,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41214
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1782310727
OL,3,CBrexit reflections: Ten years on
OL,5,F"The reality is there is an
OL,6,Finternational border between Ireland
OL,7,Fand Northern Ireland, between the
OL,8,FEuropean Union and the UK that's not
OL,9,Fin the European Union, and the sooner
OL,10,Fwe accept that and make it work
OL,11,Fproperly, the sooner we'll be able to
OL,12,Fmove on from these unsatisfactory
OL,13,Farrangements that are in place."
OL,15,FCatch up with the latest UTV Live on
OL,16,FITVX
OL,18,FSign up for our free weekly newsletter
OL,19,Fhere.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G14/14
